social_posts.post_text: No wonder it was never plugged in at all.

I shot this during a heatwave back in 2021. I woke up at around 4am covered in sweat and figured I mine as well go down to the water and shoot the sunrise that had already started to show. I was setting up my drone when I noticed a person standing on the edge of the rocks just staring out at the water for what seemed like forever. It felt like a scene out of a movie.

Hope everyone had a nice Christmas!

WARNING: 
GRAPHIC CONTENT
_________________

Walked around for about an hour and a half photographing cars and people at the @goodguysrodandcustom show in Puyallup and realized after hitting 40 on my film counter that my camera was indeed…empty of film. I had no choice but to accept this bleak, and crushing reality, wipe the sweat from the back of my knees, and load that god damn “back up roll” I had brought, not realizing it was the only roll lol. I basically tried to shoot a lot of the stuff I had originally shot from memory, but some shots I just could recreate with the cars, people, and light constantly changing. So moral of the story, always check to make sure you have film in your camera, even if you think you do, just check again, I guess. fml ttyl gn ✌️
